snippet.textDisplay: I've gotten Morgan Taylor nail polish from ULTA stores for around $10 and I've gotten good results and would buy again but I do use seche vite quick dry top coat with all of my nail polish and it is amazing and seems to turn every type of nail color into a hard smooth super long lasting almost gel like finish. I say almost because I believe it's stronger than gel polish. I always do one coat of color and let it dry some, you don't even have to let it dry all the way if you don't want to wait  just so long as it's not liquid anymore, then do one coat of seche vite which will dry in under 30 seconds and then you can repeat the process if you need to coats of color. You can also just do 2 coats of color and only put the top coat on the top, I like to use it after each coat because it fully dries and hardens the polish giving it a little more strength and substance. Let me know if you have used seche vite in a video already I'd like to hear what you think about it.
